  "overview": "An update for nbdkit is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.",
  "description": "Network Block Device (NBD) is a protocol for accessing hard disks and other disk-like devices over the network. The nbdkit toolkit utilizes NBD to create servers with minimal dependencies. The package contains plug-in support for the C and Python programming languages.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): nbdkit vddk plugin export parameter should allow loose wildcards without FNM_PATHNAME [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-137303)  Migration fails with \"plugin must set minimum block size between 1 and 64K\" on storage with minimum_io_size > 64KiB [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-140707)",
